summary: TL* THE CONTACT OWNS A 2011 TOYOTA SIENNA. THE CONTACT STATED THAT WHILE DRIVING AT APPROXIMATELY 55 MPH, THE PASSENGER SIDE SLIDING DOOR ERRONEOUSLY OPENED. THE VEHICLE WAS TAKEN TO THE TOYOTA DEALER OF DANVERS LOCATED IN DANVERS, MASSACHUSETTS BUT THE CAUSE OF THE FAILURE WAS NOT DETERMINED AND THE VEHICLE WAS NOT REPAIRED. THE MANUFACTURER WAS NOT NOTIFIED OF THE FAILURE. THE FAILURE MILEAGE WAS 58,000. THE VIN WAS INVALID.
